<item>
            <title>[LU-16234] mount.lustre  /dev/sdb1 has not been formatted with mkfs.lustre or the backend filesystem type is not supported by this tool</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16234</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Manually compiled and installed (&quot;make install&quot;)e2fsprogs doesn&apos;t install libext2fs.so.2 libraries that needed to mount.lustre and mkfs.lustre utils. As results these symptoms arrised:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mount.lustre: /dev/sdb1 has not been formatted with mkfs.lustre or the backend filesystem type is not supported by this tool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Installing e2fsprogs from rpm solves the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="72764">LU-16234</key>
            <summary>mount.lustre  /dev/sdb1 has not been formatted with mkfs.lustre or the backend filesystem type is not supported by this tool</summary>
